juancho: So you are the child from Calamba.
Rizal: I love to draw... but I am not good at it yet.
juancho: Talent is useless without practice. Show me.
juancho: You see details that others do not notice. Such an ability is rare.
Rizal: Can art do anything to change the world?
juancho: Art preserves the truth. Someday, you may need that.
